wiki.text:
'Maxx' may refer to:

* Maxx (band), a German Eurodance act
* ''Maxx'' (film), an Iranian movie
* [[The Maxx]], a comic book and animated character
* MAXX (brand), the former brand under which part of Auckland, New Zealand's
  public transport network operated
* Maxx (wrestler), the professional wrestler John Czawlytko, who used this ring
  name in WCW in the mid-late 1990s
* Maxx Almere, a bus service in Almere, the Netherlands
* Holden Captiva MaXX, a rebadged Opel Antara motor vehicle
* T.J. Maxx, a department store chain in the USA
* T.K. Maxx, a retail chain in Europe
* A line of radio-controlled vehicles from Traxxas, including the T-Maxx,
  SportMaxx, S-Maxx and E-Maxx
* Maxx (Maxx "The Wild Child" Mann), a singer in the Trans-Siberian Orchestra
